[src:saml-deep/saml-2-0-p02] Since a security context exists, the service provider returns the resource to the user agent.
[src:saml-deep/saml-2-0-p02] This is a relatively simple deployment of the SAML 2.0 Web Browser SSO Profile (SAMLProf) where both the service provider (SP) and the identity provider (IdP) use the HTTP POST binding.
[src:saml-deep/saml-2-0-p02] The message flow begins with a request for a secured resource at the SP.
[src:saml-deep/saml-2-0-p02] Before the `<samlp:AuthnRequest>` element is inserted into the XHTML form, it is first base64-encoded.
